# A malware beacon is usually:
#   outbound (internal-fw, fw-net), and may match --
#     small packets (tiny periodic UDP/TCP messages)
#     sow frequency but regular
#     destination is unusual (rare ASN, odd port, cloud IP with no business purpose)
#     protocol is unexpected (DNS, HTTPS, ICMP, or custom high ports)
#     originates from a host that normally doesnt talk to the internet

tempfile="/home/joe/tempfile"
